---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/guides" class="link text-sm">← All operator guides</a>
      <p class="editorial-kicker mt-6">Selection framework</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">How to pick a Shopify email marketing app without regret</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-stone-700">Score six dimensions before migration: lifecycle fit, Shopify data depth, pricing, team capacity, channels, migration risk.</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700/90">Constraint-first selection beats choosing the logo your agency already knows.</p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps/sequenzy">Sequenzy review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/guides/implementation-plan">Implementation plan</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/compare/sequenzy-vs-klaviyo">Sequenzy vs Klaviyo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title="Selection framework at a glance" picks={[
        { label: 'Best overall', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Lifecycle strategy and pay-per-email when operator clarity binds before raw data maximums.' },
        { label: 'Best data depth', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Predictive Shopify segmentation when catalogs and browse events drive weekly decisions.' },
        { label: 'Best fast start', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Prebuilt cart, welcome, and post-purchase when speed beats custom logic.' },
        { label: 'Best SMS pair', tool: 'Postscript', reason: 'SMS-native recovery paired with your email lifecycle layer.' },
        { label: 'This playbook', tool: 'Selection framework', reason: 'Score six dimensions before migration: lifecycle fit, Shopify data depth, pricing, team capacity, channels, migration risk.' }
    ]} />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Why Selection framework matters for Shopify email marketing apps</h2>
      <p>Selection framework is platform-agnostic operating discipline for Shopify email marketing apps. Vendor demos sell features; operators need suppressions, consent proof, and margin-aware measurement.</p>
      <p>Read this alongside <a class="link" href="/guides/selection-framework">selection framework</a> when evaluating tools and <a class="link" href="/guides/implementation-plan">implementation plan</a> when going live.</p>
      <p><strong>specialty coffee roastery.</strong> Used selection framework to cut Klaviyo profile anxiety — engaged-only sends dropped bill 38% while replenishment revenue rose.</p>
      <p><strong>dog adventure gear store.</strong> Fixed overlapping welcome and cart discounts using the checklist here — unsubscribes fell 0.2 points in one month.</p>
      <p><strong>artisan hot sauce brand.</strong> Documented selection framework in Notion so agency handoffs stopped breaking flows every catalog rename.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Operator checklist</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-stone-800">Selection framework checklist before scaling sends</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Inventory live automations with triggers, delays, and known bugs</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Document monthly send volume, profile count, and SMS credits</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Assign internal owner for post-launch flow edits</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Run one workflow on paper: trigger, audience, suppression, offer, metric</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Audit consent sources and timestamps for email and SMS</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Block major changes during BFCM prep unless incident-driven</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Implementation notes across platforms</h2>
      <p><strong>Sequenzy first.</strong> Agent-first edits compress time from strategy to live flow — ideal when the retention owner is also merchandising and support.</p>
      <p><strong>Klaviyo when data depth binds.</strong> Native Shopify events, predictive scores, and variant blocks when catalog complexity and order volume justify profile pricing.</p>
      <p><strong>Omnisend for multichannel speed.</strong> Email, SMS, and push in one builder when multichannel must go live before next product drop.</p>
      <p><strong>Postscript for SMS depth.</strong> Pair with your email layer when mobile recovery justifies cost — document channel ownership in <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">flow collision prevention</a>.</p>
      <p>Cross-read <a class="link" href="/use-cases">use-case playbooks</a> and <a class="link" href="/for">store-type guides</a> when vertical nuance changes workflow priority.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Weekly operating rhythm</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-stone-800">Cadence that keeps Selection framework honest</h2>
      <p>Monday: scan flow collision alerts and discount exposure by segment.</p>
      <p>Wednesday: segment orphan audit — any segment with no send purpose in 60 days merges or deletes.</p>
      <p>Friday: revenue and margin review per active automation, not campaign vanity metrics.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Common mistakes</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-stone-800">Five failure modes</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3">
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Treating the playbook as a one-time project instead of quarterly ops</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Copying another store’s stack without matching catalog or AOV</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Scaling sends before suppression and consent are documented</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Letting agencies own logic without internal documentation</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8 text-stone-700"><span class="text-orange-700">→</span>Optimizing open rate while margin compresses from stacked discounts</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Measurement and proof</h2>
      <p>Define one primary metric for this playbook — incremental revenue, deliverability rate, or discount exposure cap.</p>
      <p>Compare 14-day before/after when changing rules; hold out 5–10% where possible.</p>
      <p>Share results with finance using the same definition as <a class="link" href="/guides/revenue-attribution">revenue attribution</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Phase map</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-stone-800">Where Selection framework fits in your program</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3 text-stone-700">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-stone-800">Before you buy</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7">Pair with <a class="link" href="/guides/selection-framework">selection framework</a> and <a class="link" href="/guides/pricing-models">pricing models</a>. Score finalists against selection framework requirements before demos.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-stone-800">During rollout</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7">Pair with <a class="link" href="/guides/implementation-plan">implementation plan</a>, <a class="link" href="/guides/migration">migration</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">flow collision prevention</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-stone-800">Ongoing ops</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7">Revisit monthly in standups; quarterly in retention reviews with finance and support leads in the room.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Deep dive: Selection framework in three acts</h2>
      <p>Act one — diagnose. Export what you have today: live flows, segments, discount codes, consent sources, and last 90 days send volume. Selection framework fails when teams skip inventory and jump to new tooling.</p>
      <p>Act two — design. Write rules a new hire could execute: triggers, audiences, suppressions, offer caps, and metrics. Sequenzy accelerates this with agent-first prompts; Klaviyo requires explicit boolean documentation.</p>
      <p>Act three — prove. Hold out where ethical, measure incrementally, and publish results internally so merchandising stops requesting ad-hoc blasts that break selection framework discipline.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-stone-800">Platform fit for selection framework</h2>
      <table class="data-table mt-4">
        <thead><tr><th>Platform</th><th>Strength</th><th>Watch-out</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Strategy speed, pay-per-email</td><td>Pair SMS separately</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Shopify data maximums</td><td>Profile pricing at scale</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Omnisend</td><td>Fast multichannel launch</td><td>Template ceilings</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Drip</td><td>Visual workflow control</td><td>Per-contact pricing</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Postscript</td><td>SMS compliance depth</td><td>Not a full email suite</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Questions to ask vendors during selection framework evaluation</h2>
      <p>Can you express our highest-value workflow on paper — trigger, audience, suppression, offer, product context, metric — without workarounds?</p>
      <p>How does billing change at 2x list size with flat engagement? Show pay-per-email vs per-contact crossover.</p>
      <p>What happens to our deliverability if we import the full list including 40% inactive profiles?</p>
      <p>Who on our team can edit boolean logic after launch week — and does your UX match their skill path?</p>
      <p>How do you prevent welcome, cart, browse, and winback from stacking discounts in the same 72-hour window?</p>
    </div>

